<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0822 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author first discusses several nuclear realities such as: a nuclearexchange could be a catastrophe from which the globe might never recoverand there is no defense against nuclear weapons. He then discusses militaryillusions such as: nuclear weapons could be used to gain some advantagein the field war between nuclear powers, nuclear war could be a smallwar that could be contained, and nuclear war could be won. The authorconcludes that the only way for a stable state of mutual nuclear deterrenceto prevail is for there to be political compromises.</TEXT></DOC>